<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="tdf.exttempsitepolicy">


<body>
<metal:main fill-slot="main"
             tal:define="toLocalizedTime nocall:context/@@plone/toLocalizedTime;
                         cropText nocall:context/@@plone/cropText;">

    <h1 i18n:translate="">Welcom to ODFAuthors!</h1>
    <p i18n:translate="">This is a <b>development</b> site for LibreOffice documentation.</p>
    <h2 i18n:translate="">How you can help at ODFAuthors</h2>
    <p i18n:translate="">We are a group of volunteer reviewers, writers, editors, proofreader, indexers, and translators producing
documentation. You need an account to log in to the website. Please write to <b>webmaster@odfauthors</b> and request an account. (We
had to stop self-registration because of too many spam accounts.) But first! Please subscribe to the 
<a href="mailto:odfauthors-discuss-subscribe@lists.odfauthors.org">odfauthors-discuss mailing list</a> and
introduce yourself.</p>

</metal:main>

</body>
</html>
